aVThis man is supposed to represent
p20
aVa generic human being,
p21
aVand all of the circles in that man are all of the cells that make up your body.
p22
aVThere is about a trillion human cells that make each one of us
p23
aVwho we are and able to do all the things that we do,
p24
aVbut you have 10 trillion bacterial cells
p25
aVin you or on you at any moment in your life.
p26
aVSo, 10 times more bacterial cells
p27
aVthan human cells on a human being.
p28
aVAnd of course it's the DNA that counts,
p29
aVso here's all the A, T, Gs and Cs
p30
aVthat make up your genetic code, and give you all your charming characteristics.
p31
aVYou have about 30,000 genes.
