aa(lp167
VFirst we figured out how this bacterium does this,
p168
aVbut then we brought the tools of molecular biology to this
p169
aVto figure out really what's the mechanism.
p170
aVAnd what we found \u2014 so this is now supposed to be, again, my bacterial cell \u2014
p171
aVis that Vibrio fischeri has a protein \u2014
p172
aVthat's the red box \u2014 it's an enzyme that makes
p173
aVthat little hormone molecule, the red triangle.
p174
aVAnd then as the cells grow, they're all releasing that molecule
p175
aVinto the environment, so there's lots of molecule there.
p176
aVAnd the bacteria also have a receptor on their cell surface
p177
aVthat fits like a lock and key with that molecule.
p178
aVThese are just like the receptors on the surfaces of your cells.
p179
aVWhen the molecule increases to a certain amount \u2014
p180
aVwhich says something about the number of cells \u2014
p181
aVit locks down into that receptor
p182
aVand information comes into the cells
p183
aVthat tells the cells to turn on
p184
aVthis collective behavior of making light.
