aa(lp214
VWe also then went to look at what are these molecules \u2014
p215
aVthese were the red triangles on my slides before.
p216
aVThis is the Vibrio fischeri molecule.
p217
aVThis is the word that it talks with.
p218
aVSo then we started to look at other bacteria,
p219
aVand these are just a smattering of the molecules that we've discovered.
p220
aVWhat I hope you can see
p221
aVis that the molecules are related.
p222
aVThe left-hand part of the molecule is identical
p223
aVin every single species of bacteria.
p224
aVBut the right-hand part of the molecule is a little bit different in every single species.
